article.title: Dynamical timescale of precollapse evolution inferred from chemical distribution in the Taurus Molecular Cloud-1 (TMC-1) filament

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the color gradient from northwest to southeast in the 4.5 and 8 µm emission likely indicate about the TMC-1 filament?
choices: The presence of a protostar in the southeast region.
The filament is inclined towards a late B-type star, HD 29647.
A variation in gas density, with the southeast being denser.
An uneven distribution of carbon-chain molecules.

multiple_choice_question.text: In the color-color diagram (left), what evolutionary stage do the majority of the filled circles (numbered 1-5) represent?
Based on the bolometric temperature (Tbol), what is the predominant evolutionary stage of the YSO candidates listed in the table?
This formula calculates the H2 column density using dust continuum emission. What does the variable  "κ" represent in this equation?
choices: The mass opacity of dust per gram of gas
